Determine which one of the following bar graphs could represent the data from the revised circle graph:
``` 
[asy]
unitsize(36);
draw(circle((0,0),1)); 
fill((0,0)--arc((0,0),(0,1),(-1,0))--cycle,lightgray); 
fill((0,0)--arc((0,0),(-1,0),(0,-1))--cycle,gray); 
fill((0,0)--arc((0,0),(0,-1),(1,0))--cycle,black); 
fill((0,0)--arc((0,0),(1,0),(0,1))--cycle,white); 
```
This circle graph is divided into four parts: white, black, gray, and light gray. The light gray part is half the size of the gray part, the gray part is half the size of the black part, and the black part is half the size of the white part.
A. Bars with heights proportional to 50%, 25%, 12.5%, and 6.25%
B. Bars with heights proportional to 25%, 50%, 12.5%, and 6.25%
C. Bars all with equal heights
D. Bars with heights not corresponding to any proper scaling of the sections
